Celebrating Women on International Women’s Day! ❤️ Meet the Om Banna Group of women from Gagadi in Rajasthan. They are one of the many groups Zaggora has helped over the last couple of years through our Giving programme. We taught the women from the Om Banna Group to make door decorations which were sold at the local market and helped them make a profit, get a bank account and start saving. Our Giving programme helps women and their communities to build a better life. We also donated bicycles to the daughters of the Om Banna women, to help them get to school, helping them learn more and giving them better opportunity.
We can all do our little bit to help the world be more connected and lift each other. On this International Women’s Day let’s be grateful for the women on whose shoulders we stand today, and build a strong foundation for our daughters and grand daughters in the future. ❤️❤️❤️

Alcohol. Our second day of exploring the other side of commonly perceived vices. While alcohol in excess is harmful to health, alcohol enjoyed in small amounts can have positive impact on our insulin response (reducing the risk of diabetes) and production of good cholesterol. At Zaggora we are big believers that health should be achieved primarily through enjoyment, moderation and joy. And a little treat every once in a while can only be good for the body and soul. 🥂🥂🥂
